dc:source  a    owl:AnnotationProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_4728  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 4: Confocal imaging of hippocampal neuronal cultures with co-staining for Homer1c-mCherry and CPG2-GFP (CPG2/SYNE1) show this protein is localized at the postsynapse.\n\nFigure 5: time-lapse experiments on neurons co-expressing Homer1c and fluorophore-tagged CPG2 showed high association with PSDs.\n\nFigure 7: Shank knockdown reduced clathrin-positive PSDs and association of some endocytic proteins with PSD, but not CPG2 for which EZ localizating is seemingly independent of PSD-EZ coupling via Shank. \"Unfortunately for CPG2, we were not able to obtain high-density localization maps and were unable to draw any conclusions about the nanoscale organization of CPG2 at the EZ.\". Experimental description: M&M: \"Hippocampal cultures were prepared from brain of embryonic day 18 (E18) Wistar rats (both genders) as described before (Scheefhals et al., 2019)\"\n\nGFP-CPG2 was obtained by replacing the HA-tag in the HA-CPG2 construct (gift from Dr. Nedivi) using Gibson assembly. shCPG2 was a gift from Dr. Nedivi.\n\nregarding the target protein sequence;\n\nCottrell JR, et al. \"CPG2: a brain- and synapse-specific protein that regulates the endocytosis of glutamate receptors\" Neuron. 2004. PMID:15541315\n\n\"Mouse monoclonal anti-CPG2 antibody 200A6.1 (IgG1) was generated against the peptide RKLESTLTGLEQSRERQERR (ResGen)\"\nWhich refers to sigma Anti-SYNE1 Antibody, clone 200A6, MABN857.\nWhich in turn links to uniprot ID Q63128 (supposed brain-specific splice variant of SYNE1)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2022-08-01" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4728" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

